{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa195\cf1\b\f0\fs20 XMLGetAlias()\cf2  returns the alias associated with a URI within some XML. \par
To use this example, use the\i\f1  Fill XML \i0\f0 and\i\f1  Edit Raw XML\i0\f0  buttons to create and edit the XML file. Then use the \i\f1 GetAlias\i0\f0  button to bring up a form which allows you to query the XML using \cf1 XMLGetAlias()\cf2 .\par
