{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}{\f1\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue128;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa195\cf1\b\f0\fs20 XMLGetAlias()\cf2  returns the alias associated with a URI within some XML. \par
To use this example, select a URI and namespace, then press the \i\f1 XMLSetNS() \i0\f0 button. Note that you can only do this once per URI/Namespace combination, or you will get an error message. \par
Then, press the\i\f1  XMLGetAlias()\i0\f0  button to see how the new alias gets returned.\par
You can view the raw XML to see how these values are stored in the XML.\par
}
